        <headline>Extreme Heat Watch issued June 7 at 1:00PM MDT until June 10 at 10:00PM MDT by NWS Boise ID</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Dangerously hot conditions with temperatures up to 100
possible. Winds will be light, so very little breeze will be
available to aid in cooling off.

* WHERE...Oregon Lower Treasure Valley.

* WHEN...From Monday afternoon through Tuesday evening.

* IMPACTS...Extreme heat will significantly increase the potential
for heat-related illnesses, particularly for those working or
participating in outdoor activities.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates.

Do not leave young children and pets in unattended vehicles. Car
interiors will reach lethal temperatures in a matter of minutes.</instruction>
